two reasons not to accept
it -- one, because you don't
understand the technical details

10:11.267 --> 10:15.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because you don't have
to skills, or because you
don't want to understand
it for political

10:15.633 --> 10:17.100 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
reasons.

10:17.100 --> 10:18.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Well, you do have
the technical expertise.

10:18.567 --> 10:21.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Does it hold up for you?

10:21.667 --> 10:24.467 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
RID: Yes.

10:24.467 --> 10:29.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, what I do is I look
at specific cases and I drill
down and I zoom into the

10:31.200 --> 10:34.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
details of the picture
and look at that detail.

10:34.867 --> 10:39.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we can often link specific
cases like the one that
Dmitri was just describing to

10:41.967 --> 10:45.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
another case because the tool
set that they're using is the
same, really like the tool of

10:47.900 --> 10:51.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the burglar that breaks into
one building and uses the
same or a comparable tool in

10:51.867 --> 10:53.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
another building.

10:53.933 --> 10:57.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, one thing that I'm, for
instance, interested in and that
I focused on is how they broke

10:59.433 --> 11:02.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into the German parliament and
that we can link that to the
DNC and, indeed, we can also

11:02.267 --> 11:03.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
link those two cases.

11:03.933 --> 11:05.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, the evidence is
really strong that we
have at this point.

11:05.933 --> 11:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: So, the
evidence is really strong.

11:07.733 --> 11:12.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Are you saying there is just no
doubt about it, at this point?

11:12.600 --> 11:17.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RID: Among people who
studied the true forensic
evidence, among people
who do incident response,

11:20.133 --> 11:23.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the vast majority of this
community -- and, you
know, bear in mind this
is an entire profession

11:23.900 --> 11:28.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
trained to do digital
investigations -- most
people in that profession
accept the evidence

11:29.500 --> 11:31.533 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that we have.

11:31.533 --> 11:35.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's really not controversial
anymore that we're looking
at a major Russian campaign.

11:35.433 --> 11:38.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know, keep in mind: this has
been going on for many years.

11:38.300 --> 11:42.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This particular act, that we
watched them for eight years,
and over the past year, they

11:42.433 --> 11:45.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
made quite a lot of mistakes
which revealed themselves.

11:45.133 --> 11:50.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Now, Dmitri
Alperovitch, we want
to point out and we
said earlier, you were

11:51.733 --> 11:53.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
- - your company was
the one that uncovered
this in the first place.

11:53.533 --> 11:56.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You were working for the
Democratic National Committee.

11:56.300 --> 11:58.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Are you still working
-- doing work for them?

11:58.533 --> 12:00.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ALPEROVITCH: We're protecting
them going forward.

12:00.433 --> 12:02.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The investigation is closed in
terms of what happened there.

12:02.867 --> 12:07.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But certainly, we've
seen the campaigns,
political organizations are
continued to be targeted,

12:07.400 --> 12:11.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and they continue to hire
us and use our technology
to protect themselves.

12:11.100 --> 12:14.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: I ask you that
because if there's a question
of conflict of interest, how do

12:14.367 --> 12:15.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you answer that?

12:15.800 --> 12:17.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ALPEROVITCH: Well, this
report was not about the DNC.

12:17.867 --> 12:21.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
This report was about
information we uncovered
about what these Russian
actors were doing

12:21.933 --> 12:26.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in eastern Ukraine in terms
of locating these artillery
units of the Ukrainian army and

12:26.633 --> 12:28.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
then targeting them.

12:28.733 --> 12:32.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, what we just did is said
that it looks exactly as the
same to the evidence we've

12:32.267 --> 12:34.767 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
already uncovered from the
DNC, linking the two together.

12:34.767 --> 12:39.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: So, if there's still
someone out there like the
president-elect or others who

12:39.233 --> 12:44.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
support him who say, we just
don't believe this, we don't
think it's been proven, we

12:44.233 --> 12:48.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
haven't seen the CIA and the
FBI's information, what's
your response to that?

12:48.967 --> 12:51.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALPEROVITCH: Well, I think it's
legitimate to ask questions
and this is why we wanted

12:51.467 --> 12:55.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to produce more evidence that
raises the level of confidence
that we have, even internally,

12:55.933 --> 12:58.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that this is Russian
intelligence agency
called the GRU.

12:58.700 --> 13:01.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think it's also important
for the government to
release their own evidence.

13:01.500 --> 13:03.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And I'm encouraged
that President Obama
ordered this review.

13:03.533 --> 13:07.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I hope the report that comes
out will be made public so that
everyone can look at it and

13:07.267 --> 13:09.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
make their own judgments.

13:09.233 --> 13:12.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Thomas Rid, what
more would you need to see,
what more a skeptic need to see

13:12.700 --> 13:17.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in order to erase all doubt?

13:17.133 --> 13:22.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RID: Of course, we can always
see more evidence and look for
more details, for instance on

13:24.500 --> 13:29.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
specific names of operators,
and we know that, you know, some
intelligence agencies in the

13:30.700 --> 13:32.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
United States seem to
have that information.

13:32.600 --> 13:34.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But let's keep
something in mind.

13:34.633 --> 13:38.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What they want to achieve --
what this Russian operation is
trying to achieve at this point

13:38.567 --> 13:43.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is to drive a wedge between
the president-elect, between
the next administration
and the intelligence

13:44.400 --> 13:46.467 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
community.

13:46.467 --> 13:50.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so far, if you see that as
part of the operation, they have
been spectacularly successful.

13:52.267 --> 13:55.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, releasing more evidence and
then having critics possibly
even the president-elect

13:55.033 --> 13:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
say, well, that's not good
enough, that is exactly the
outcome that they want because

13:59.133 --> 14:03.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
it introduces friction
inside the security
establishment in Washington.

14:03.833 --> 14:05.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Just quickly.

14:05.033 --> 14:06.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Dmitri, is that what
you see as well?

14:06.600 --> 14:10.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ALPEROVITCH: I think
it's important to
bring out the evidence.

14:10.633 --> 14:13.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some people legitimately
have questions about this.

14:13.033 --> 14:17.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's important for the U.S.
government to tell us what they
know because they have access

14:17.367 --> 14:22.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to classified intelligence and
sourcing methods that we are not
privy to as a private security

14:22.000 --> 14:24.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
company.

14:24.133 --> 14:26.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I think it's important to
know what happened in the most
consequential hack we've ever

14:26.467 --> 14:28.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
seen.

14:28.433 --> 14:29.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, of course,
we have no way of knowing if
that's what they will do -- what

14:29.400 --> 14:31.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
they will do.

14:31.400 --> 14:35.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, of course, we will continue
to watch it very closely, as
well you Dmitri Alperovitch,

14:35.167 --> 14:36.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Professor Thomas Rid.

14:36.167 --> 14:38.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We thank you both.

14:38.200 --> 14:43.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ALPEROVITCH: Thank you.

14:43.667 --> 14:45.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

14:45.733 --> 14:50.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Anis Amri, the
man suspected of carrying out
Monday's attack on a Berlin

14:52.733 --> 14:55.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Christmas market, was well
known to German authorities.

14:55.933 --> 15:00.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was under surveillance
for six months this year and
was slated for deportation.

15:00.733 --> 15:04.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But his home country of
Tunisia refused to accept him.

15:04.133 --> 15:08.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Joining me now for more on how
Amri allegedly was allowed to
pull off this attack is Peter

15:08.033 --> 15:12.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Neumann, founder and director
of the International Center for
the Study of Radicalization and

15:12.200 --> 15:13.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Political Violence.

15:13.300 --> 15:15.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He joins us tonight from Munich.

15:15.133 --> 15:17.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What's the latest in
the investigation?

15:17.500 --> 15:19.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER NEUMANN, INTERNATIONAL
CENTER FOR THE STUDY
OF RADICALIZATION AND
POLITICAL VIOLENCE:

15:19.633 --> 15:23.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, the latest is that they
are still trying to track down
where exactly he is right now,

15:23.200 --> 15:28.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and they are conducting raids
on different places that are
connected to the jihadist

15:30.667 --> 15:32.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
scene.

15:32.700 --> 15:36.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It is now known that he was
part of a wider network of
jihadists in Germany, and they

15:38.633 --> 15:42.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are raiding different places
that they seem to be believing
that they are connected to

15:44.033 --> 15:46.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the scene.

15:46.033 --> 15:50.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Tell me, how is it
possible the German authorities
not just had this person

15:50.200 --> 15:53.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on the radar but were
scheduling him for deportation?

15:53.433 --> 15:54.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
How did it get this far?

15:54.433 --> 15:55.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How did they miss the signs?

15:55.667 --> 15:57.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
NEUMANN: So, there are
a couple of things.

15:57.667 --> 15:59.967 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The first thing is capacity.

15:59.967 --> 16:04.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are around 550 jihadists
in Germany who are believed
to be potential terrorists.

16:08.867 --> 16:13.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In order to surveil a single
person 24 hours a day, you
need about 20 officials.

16:15.900 --> 16:17.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's not possible.

16:17.967 --> 16:22.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, you know, authorities
need to make judgment calls
all the time -- who do they

16:23.933 --> 16:26.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
consider to be acutely
dangerous and who do they
consider to be less dangerous.

16:26.567 --> 16:30.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And this one may have
fallen through the net.

16:30.800 --> 16:33.467 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The second point is federalism.

16:33.467 --> 16:38.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Police and intelligence
services are essentially
on a state-by-state basis.

16:40.500 --> 16:43.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And this guy traveled
from a lot of different
states to different
states, and some of the

16:43.233 --> 16:46.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
information may have slipped
through the cracks there.

16:46.100 --> 16:50.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: What about the
possibility he was radicalized
in an Italian prison?

16:50.200 --> 16:52.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
That's something one of
his brothers had said.

16:52.833 --> 16:57.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NEUMANN: Yes, he was in an
Italian prison about four
years, and it may well be that

16:59.333 --> 17:00.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
he was radicalized there.

17:00.900 --> 17:04.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He went further up north
to Germany afterwards.

17:04.433 --> 17:09.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He shouldn't have been able to
do that because he was claiming
asylum in Germany, and coming

17:10.900 --> 17:13.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from Italy, that claim should
have been refused immediately.

17:13.800 --> 17:17.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And so, basically, the
whole system has failed.

17:17.967 --> 17:22.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think it's all down to
the fact that Germany is not
really used to being the target

17:24.533 --> 17:26.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of terrorist attacks.

17:26.467 --> 17:30.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's a little bit like
America before 9/11.

17:30.300 --> 17:33.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Germans are quite naive
still about terrorism.

17:33.033 --> 17:37.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We haven't been confronted with
the kind of terrorist attacks
other countries have been

17:37.533 --> 17:42.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
confronted with, and the whole
system has not been geared
up to confront this kind of

17:43.667 --> 17:45.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
threat.

17:45.700 --> 17:47.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Now, post-9/11,
the American system geared
up, to use your phrase.

17:47.667 --> 17:52.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, how does Germany's
sensitive history with the
surveillance state play into all

17:52.033 --> 17:54.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of this?

17:54.033 --> 17:58.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NEUMANN: That's a very good
point because ultimately, after
the end of the Second World

18:00.267 --> 18:04.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
War, Germans before reeducated
to be against surveillance
and to be pacifists.

18:05.267 --> 18:06.767 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And guess what?

18:06.767 --> 18:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
America and the ally succeeded.

18:09.033 --> 18:13.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Germans by and large
are against surveillance
and they are pacifists.

18:13.133 --> 18:18.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that means that when being
confronted with this kind of
threat, a lot of reactions

18:20.067 --> 18:23.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by politicians but also by
society are very much against
kind of confronting this threat

18:25.333 --> 18:27.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
head on.

18:27.333 --> 18:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I very much hope that after
this incident, the pendulum
doesn't swing entirely the other

18:33.600 --> 18:38.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
way, but that we are able to
have a reasonable debate about
what kind of measures are really

18:39.800 --> 18:44.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
necessary to confront
this rather than staying
one side or the other.

18:46.200 --> 18:49.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Do you see changes
happening now in the interest
of public safety that's

18:49.467 --> 18:51.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
swinging the pendulum?

18:51.000 --> 18:53.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NEUMANN: I think there is
a lot of debate right now.

18:53.467 --> 18:58.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A lot of people are very
unhappy with how the authorities
have dealt with this case.

19:00.533 --> 19:05.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There is a sense of
real outrage, and there
is a sense that the
system isn't working and

19:06.767 --> 19:08.967 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that we really need to think
about how to make this work.

19:08.967 --> 19:13.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I believe it's necessary
to basically have something
like the 9/11 Commission that

19:15.933 --> 19:19.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you had in America after 9/11
that basically goes through
I've aspect of government policy

19:22.000 --> 19:25.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and says, this works,
this doesn't work, and
how do we construct a
comprehensive counterterrorism

19:27.167 --> 19:28.367 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
strategy?

19:28.367 --> 19:29.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We don't have that
in Germany right now.

19:29.967 --> 19:32.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We don't have a
counterterrorism strategy.

19:32.700 --> 19:35.767 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have a lot of authorities
working on different things.

19:35.767 --> 19:40.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We need a comprehensive thing,
and I hope that's what's
going to come out of this.

19:41.500 --> 19:42.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SREENIVASAN: All right.

19:42.767 --> 19:46.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Peter Neumann -- thanks
so much for joining us.

19:46.167 --> 19:51.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
NEUMANN: Thank you.

