29:55.333 --> 29:57.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
doing business in New
York city, now doing
it on the global stage.

29:57.433 --> 30:02.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, Judy, this contract
for the F-35 was done years ago,
of course, with the Pentagon

30:02.000 --> 30:04.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and Lockheed Martin.

30:04.033 --> 30:07.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's going to take days to
decipher what he's trying to say
on Twitter, but trying to create

30:07.800 --> 30:09.867 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the sense of a bidding war.

30:09.867 --> 30:14.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, this is exactly what
his voters wanted to see crump
do and he's using Twitter in

30:14.033 --> 30:16.067 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
an entirely new way to do it.

30:16.067 --> 30:20.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And, by the way, you
know, Sean Spicer, the
new press secretary,
says this will continue

30:20.167 --> 30:22.100 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
once Trump is in
the White House.

30:22.100 --> 30:26.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We'll see about that idea
that he's going to be more
restrained once he's in charge.

30:26.133 --> 30:31.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Brian Stelter,
Jeff Mason, thank you.

30:35.467 --> 30:38.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
STELTER: Thanks.

30:38.900 --> 30:43.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SREENIVASAN: This week,
Washington, D.C. passed
one of the most generous
paid family leave

30:44.667 --> 30:47.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
laws in the country.

30:47.233 --> 30:50.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The district now joins
California, Rhode Island,
New Jersey and New York
in approving similar

30:51.300 --> 30:52.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
measures.

30:52.833 --> 30:54.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Our economics correspondent
Paul Solman has the story.

30:54.833 --> 30:57.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's part of our weekly series,
"Making Sense," which airs
Thursdays on the "NewsHour".

30:57.633 --> 31:00.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
