maintain traditions handed
down the generations.

40:15.467 --> 40:19.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Here, Sundays are for
devotions to the saints,
not for worshipping at
the altar of profit.

40:22.067 --> 40:26.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The city's bishop has condemned
Sunday shopping as an act
of war with the church.

40:26.533 --> 40:31.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But in Saint Evangalistra
Church, Father Yiorgios
Yiorgakopoulos is more measured.

40:31.400 --> 40:35.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
YIORGIOS YIORGAKOPOULOS,
SAINT EVANGALISTRA
CHURCH (translated):
We are of the opinion

40:35.233 --> 40:39.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from a religious point of
view that the sixth day
of the week is provided
to man for communication

40:39.633 --> 40:43.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with God but also that attempts
are being made to get rid
of what we know as normal

40:43.967 --> 40:46.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
life.

40:46.033 --> 40:48.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
To try and turn us into robots
and machines by making all
the days the same, every day

40:48.933 --> 40:52.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a working day -- all
days without meaning.

40:52.167 --> 40:56.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: And this is the
heart of Piraeus' shopping
district on a Sunday morning.

40:56.700 --> 40:58.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Everything is firmly shuttered.

40:58.833 --> 41:03.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the International Monetary
Fund believes it's time for
this particular trade barrier

41:03.033 --> 41:05.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to be lifted.

41:05.100 --> 41:09.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED MALE: Liberalizing
the trade market will allow for
small and medium enterprises

41:10.633 --> 41:13.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to get an advantage in
the market by allowing
them to open on Sundays.

41:13.933 --> 41:18.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: One man who'd like to
use a sharp implement on what he
regards as Greece's restrictive

41:18.800 --> 41:23.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
trading practices is Notis
Mitarakis, a conservative
opposition politician who
used to be a development

41:25.467 --> 41:27.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
minister.

41:27.600 --> 41:28.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NOTIS MITARAKIS, CONSERVATIVE
LAWMAKER: Allowing people the
right to work is a fundamental

41:28.967 --> 41:32.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
right in our system of economy.

41:32.100 --> 41:37.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In order to get out of the
crisis, the key parameter is
to increase production, is to

41:37.700 --> 41:39.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
increase GDP.

41:39.833 --> 41:42.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And anything that can help to
that direction, anything that
allows people who are willing

41:42.133 --> 41:47.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and able to work, to
get out and get into
the market, is positive.

41:49.233 --> 41:52.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BRABANT: This mall is
a compelling memorial
to the corpse that
is the Greek economy.

41:54.133 --> 41:57.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's on Stadiou Street,
once Athens most expensive
shopping thoroughfare.

41:57.333 --> 42:02.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was never exactly Fifth
Avenue, but before the crisis
it was throbbing and thriving.

42:04.300 --> 42:07.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Greece's mom and pop businesses
have really taken a battering
during this seven-year-long

42:07.200 --> 42:09.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
financial crisis.

42:09.300 --> 42:13.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In all, a quarter of a
million small and medium
sized enterprises have
closed down, throwing

42:15.700 --> 42:19.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
half a million people onto
the streets and into the
vast army of the unemployed.

42:19.067 --> 42:24.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Despite vigorous oppositions
from trades unions and
the church, shopkeepers
were given permission

42:25.967 --> 42:28.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to open for a handful of
Sundays each year at special
times like Christmas.

42:28.033 --> 42:31.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But according to
business leaders, this
has made absolutely no
difference at all to the

42:31.467 --> 42:33.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
level of trading.

42:33.533 --> 42:37.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In its heyday, store owners
would pay up to $1,500 a square
feet for retail space on Stadiou

42:39.900 --> 42:41.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Street.

42:41.933 --> 42:45.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In amongst the boarded up
shells of former businesses on
Stadiou, Andreas Papagiogiou

42:45.900 --> 42:50.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is clinging on, just for the
sake of his 35-year-old son
who will inherit the shop.

42:52.900 --> 42:57.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Papagiogiou has been here for
40 years and on the day we
met, he had sold goods worth

42:57.833 --> 43:00.467 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
just 60 dollars.

43:00.467 --> 43:03.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANDREAS PAPAGIOGIOU,
STORE OWNER (translated):
Opening on a Sunday so
far has benefited nobody.

43:04.567 --> 43:06.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We're making a loss.

43:06.600 --> 43:10.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We can't afford to bring in
the staff because we can't
pay them a Sunday rate.

43:10.100 --> 43:15.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: This is Ermou, now
Athens main retail street, on a
Sunday before Christmas, which

43:16.133 --> 43:17.867 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
explains the large crowds.

43:17.867 --> 43:20.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But many of them were
just window shopping.

43:20.933 --> 43:22.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People weren't over laden
with Christmas goodies.

43:22.933 --> 43:27.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED MALE: The Sunday
opening, of course, is creating
more, let's say, expenses

43:29.867 --> 43:34.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the companies because they
have to pay 75 percent more
to their employees for the

43:36.700 --> 43:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Sunday working compared
to the other working days.

43:40.233 --> 43:45.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Therefore for the small sized
companies, this is something
that they cannot afford.

43:47.233 --> 43:51.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: Vassilis Korkidis
is the head of the country's
Small Business Federation.

43:51.467 --> 43:56.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Korkidis claims that Sunday
trading would only benefit
multinational corporations and

43:58.400 --> 44:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
outlets like Athens main
mall, which he says can afford
premium wages on a Sunday.

44:03.533 --> 44:05.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
VASSILIS, KORKIDIS, PRESIDENT,
SMALL BUSINESS FEDERATION:
The life of a small and medium

44:05.167 --> 44:07.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
sized entrepreneur
is a nightmare.

44:07.067 --> 44:12.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He has to live every day
in order to pay taxes.

44:13.500 --> 44:17.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We pay almost 65 percent
of our turnover for taxes.

44:19.400 --> 44:22.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The 35 percent left is not
enough actually to run a
business for your family to live

44:25.000 --> 44:27.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and to buy growth.

44:27.100 --> 44:31.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: Greece's plight was
high on President Obama's list
of priorities when he visited

44:32.000 --> 44:33.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Athens just after the election.

44:33.700 --> 44:35.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He made it clear that
Greeks deserves a break.

44:35.767 --> 44:40.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, PRESIDENT OF THE
UNITED STATES: In order to make
reforms sustainable the Greek

44:40.300 --> 44:45.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
economy needs the space
to return to growth and
start creating jobs again.

44:46.467 --> 44:49.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The IMF has said that
debt relief is crucial.

44:49.867 --> 44:54.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I will continue to urge
creditors to take the
steps needed to put
Greece on a path towards

44:56.767 --> 44:59.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a durable economic recovery
because it's in all of our
interests that Greece succeeds.

45:02.533 --> 45:06.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: Greece's beleaguered
prime minister, Alexis Tsipras,
has angered the country's

45:06.100 --> 45:08.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
creditors by repeatedly
reneging on promises.

45:08.933 --> 45:12.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALEXIS TSIPRAS, PRIME MINISTER,
GREECE (through translator): The
Greek economy and our society,

45:12.600 --> 45:16.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
after seven whole years,
cannot take any more austerity.

45:16.200 --> 45:21.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: But the European Union,
which has provided most of
Greece's bail out cash ignored

45:21.933 --> 45:23.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the U.S. president.

45:23.867 --> 45:28.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Analyst Nick Malkoutzis
believes that any recovery will
be further delayed while the

45:28.100 --> 45:31.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
IMF and European Union disagree
over what is the next step.

45:31.833 --> 45:36.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NICK MALKOUTZIS, ANALYST: The
Europeans are reluctant to
provide the debt relief that

45:38.000 --> 45:40.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Greece needs because
of political reasons.

45:40.867 --> 45:45.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The IMF is reluctant to back
down on what it sees as the
structural side which it thinks

45:47.033 --> 45:49.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is very important
moving forward.

45:49.333 --> 45:50.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's wrong and
right on both sides.

45:50.733 --> 45:53.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The problem is Greece is
caught between the two.

45:53.633 --> 45:58.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The finance minister likened it
to be being trapped between two
elephants that were fighting

45:58.400 --> 46:02.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and that's the reality
for Greece at the moment.

46:02.033 --> 46:06.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BRABANT: The financial
crisis may mean hardship
that will last a generation.

46:06.400 --> 46:11.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But at St. Evangelistra's
Church, theologian Ilias Liamis
was resolute over the issue of

46:12.367 --> 46:14.367 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Sunday trading.

46:14.367 --> 46:18.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ILIAS LIAMIS, THEOLOGIAN
(through translator): This is an
attempt to eradicate the better

46:20.467 --> 46:23.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
things in life -- the joy of
meeting up with a friend ,the
joy of having a day when your

46:23.733 --> 46:28.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
mind will not be occupied solely
with numbers, cash and consumer
goods, the concept of having

46:29.900 --> 46:31.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a day to relax and
rest one's soul.

46:31.967 --> 46:36.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This concept seems to be
considered as something
that should no longer exist.

46:36.033 --> 46:40.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The important thing here is
that this is a challenge urging
us to change the way we think.

46:40.833 --> 46:44.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YIORGAKOPOULOS (through
translator): The crisis is
basically a spiritual one.

46:44.767 --> 46:48.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
People themselves decide how
they will live their lives, just
as those older than us lived

46:48.633 --> 46:50.267 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
with less and were happy.

46:50.267 --> 46:54.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So will we learn to live with
less money and still be happy.

46:54.133 --> 46:59.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
BRABANT: This woman is
unburdening her troubles
to Saint Spyridon.

47:01.133 --> 47:04.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Elsewhere millions of Greeks
are crying silent tears of anger
at what they perceive as the

47:05.733 --> 47:07.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
injustice of a never
ending financial crisis.

47:07.933 --> 47:12.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour", I'm
Malcolm Brabant in Athens.

47:13.533 --> 47:18.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEOTAPE)

47:20.100 --> 47:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Finally tonight,
an author channeling his inner
child through graphic novels.

47:25.133 --> 47:28.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown sits down with
Gene Luen Yang, one of this
year's MacArthur Genius Award

47:28.867 --> 47:29.867 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
winners.

47:29.867 --> 47:31.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

47:31.900 --> 47:32.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GENE LUEN YANG, AMBASSADOR
FOR YOUNG PEOPLE'S LITERATURE:
I'm super excited to be here

47:32.567 --> 47:33.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with you.

47:33.933 --> 47:36.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
My name is gene.

47:36.033 --> 47:37.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN, PBS NEWSHOUR
CORRESPONDENT: Gene Luen Yang
can seem like one of the kids

47:37.800 --> 47:39.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
himself.

47:39.000 --> 47:41.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
YANG: This is what I
look like in real life.

47:41.133 --> 47:44.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is what I look like as
a cartoon and this morning,
what I'm going to do is I'm

47:44.733 --> 47:48.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going to share with you
about two things that I love.

47:48.233 --> 47:53.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: Sharing things he loves
is now part of his official job
description, as the national

47:55.233 --> 47:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ambassador for Young People's
Literature, an honor given
him by the Library of Congress

47:58.300 --> 48:00.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
earlier this year.

48:00.200 --> 48:02.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And the two things he loves?

48:02.400 --> 48:04.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Comic books and coding.

48:04.433 --> 48:08.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We spoke recently as he
visited Stonewall Middle
School in Manassas, Virginia.

48:08.433 --> 48:10.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
YANG: I think
they're so related.

48:10.567 --> 48:15.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Coding and writing stories,
I really feel like I use the
same parts of my brain to do

48:15.867 --> 48:17.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
both, right?

48:17.833 --> 48:20.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When you're making a comic what
you do if you take a fairly
complex storyline, and you

48:20.367 --> 48:22.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
have to break it up
into individual panels.

48:22.567 --> 48:24.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And coding is very
much the same way.

48:24.533 --> 48:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You take a complex concept
and you break it up
into individual lines.

48:28.233 --> 48:32.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it's all about taking the
complex and breaking it into
simple, understandable pieces.

48:32.400 --> 48:36.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: I don't think everybody
thinks of it that way, thinks
of the connection between

48:36.200 --> 48:38.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
writing and coding.

48:38.133 --> 48:42.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: I think there is a
tendency in modern American
culture to separate the sciences

48:44.300 --> 48:47.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
from the arts, and to
me it just feels like
such a false dichotomy.

48:47.967 --> 48:50.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
You know, there are
so many people who are
interested in both.

48:50.500 --> 48:54.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are so many people
pursuing both and who want
to become good at both.

48:54.600 --> 48:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: Yang began drawing as
a young child and creating
comics and graphic novels by

48:59.133 --> 49:01.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
fifth grade.

49:01.233 --> 49:05.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The son of Chinese immigrants,
he grew up in California,
majoring in computer science

49:06.267 --> 49:07.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
at U.C.

49:07.500 --> 49:09.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Berkeley with a minor
in creative writing.

49:09.533 --> 49:14.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He taught computer science at
an Oakland, California high
school for 17 years before

49:15.133 --> 49:17.167 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
turning to full-time writing.

49:17.167 --> 49:21.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In 2006, his "American
Born Chinese" became
the first graphic novel
to be nominated for

49:22.700 --> 49:25.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a National Book Award.

49:25.167 --> 49:29.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And the two-volume
"Boxers and Saints,"
about the boxer rebellion
in China, also received

49:30.200 --> 49:32.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a nomination, in 2013.

49:32.400 --> 49:36.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
What is it about comics,
or graphic novels,
that somehow works?

49:36.500 --> 49:38.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Because not everybody
gets it, right?

49:38.433 --> 49:39.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
YANG: Yes, yes, yes.

49:39.933 --> 49:43.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For me, I love the combination
of the visual with the text.

49:43.733 --> 49:48.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And as a reader, I just
think that the interplay
between pictures and
words can be so complex.

49:50.767 --> 49:53.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, like in the hands of
a really good cartoonist, you
can get some really amazing

49:53.433 --> 49:55.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
things out.

49:55.500 --> 49:59.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROWN: I see you with the kids
and you play up their kind
of insecurities that you had,

50:00.600 --> 50:01.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
right, you're very
upfront about that.

50:01.667 --> 50:02.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
YANG: Yes.

50:02.933 --> 50:04.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BROWN: "I'm a nerd, I
was this, I was that."

50:04.733 --> 50:06.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Why?

50:06.000 --> 50:08.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
YANG: Well, first,
because it's true!

50:08.900 --> 50:12.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think, this is what I realized
as an adult, as somebody who
